 Converting Text to Speech with Amazon Polly
Step 1: Access Amazon Polly
Log in to AWS Management Console

Visit the AWS Management Console.
Enter your AWS credentials to log in.
Navigate to Amazon Polly

In the AWS Management Console, search for “Amazon Polly” and select it.
Step 2: Create Speech Synthesis Task
Input Text

Enter the text you want to convert into speech.
Select Voice and Language

Choose from available voices and languages.
Configure speech settings, such as speech rate and volume.
Synthesize Speech

Click “Synthesize speech” to generate the audio.
Step 3: Download or Stream Audio
Access Generated Audio
Download the generated audio file or stream it directly to your application.
Free Tier Limit: 5 million characters of text-to-speech per month for the first 12 months.
